## Performance Guidelines

### Memoization (When Needed)

```javascript
// ✅ CORRECT: Use useMemo for expensive calculations
const expensiveValue = useMemo(() => {
  return jobs.filter(job => job.salary > 50000);
}, [jobs]);

// ✅ CORRECT: Use useCallback for stable function references
const handleClick = useCallback(() => {
  navigate('/jobs');
}, [navigate]);

// Don't overuse - only when performance is actually needed
```

### Avoid Unnecessary Re-renders

```javascript
// ✅ CORRECT: Extract components to prevent re-renders
function JobList({ jobs }) {
  return (
    <div>
      {jobs.map(job => (
        <JobCard key={job.id} job={job} />
      ))}
    </div>
  );
}

// JobCard only re-renders when its job prop changes
function JobCard({ job }) {
  return <div>{job.title}</div>;
}
```

## Remember

- **Always** use PascalCase for components and files
- **Always** use `.jsx` extension for files containing JSX (required for Vite)
- **Always** include `.jsx` extension in component imports
- **Always** use camelCase for variables and functions
- **Always** use kebab-case for CSS classes
- **Always** organize imports in the specified order
- **Always** use meaningful variable and function names
- **Always** prefer CSS classes over inline styles for static styling
- **Always** include comments for non-obvious logic
